headline.main: The Slaver Wildfire.; SPECIAL MESSAGE OF IRRESIDENT BUCHANAN.

docs.lead_paragraph: To the Senate and House of Representatives: On the 26th day of April last, Lieut. CRAVEN, of the United States steamer Mohawk, captured the slaver Wildfire, on the coast of Cuba, with five hundren and seven African negroes on board. The prize was brought into Key West on the 30th April, and the negroes were delivered into the custody of FERNANDO J. MORENO, Marshal of the Southern District of Florida.

headline.main: CITY INSPECTOR'S OFFICE.; REPORT UPON THE SANITARY PRECAUTIONS REQUIRED BY THE APPROACHING SUMMER.

docs.lead_paragraph: The subjoined report was prepared by Mr. DANIEL E. DELEVAN, the City Inspector, in order to be submitted to the Board of Aldermen at its regular meeting yesterday. A failure of a quorum, however, prevented the transaction of business by this Board. The subject is too important to be postponed, and we, therefore, lay the paper before our readers in advance.

headline.main: BROOKLYN INTELLIGENCE.; Proceedings of the Common Council.

docs.lead_paragraph: A regular meeting of the Board of Aldermen was held last evening. A communication was received from Mayor POWELL, calling attention to the necessity of making some preparation for a YellowFever Hospital. The subject was referred to the Health Committee.
